!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

dumb /dʌm/

(dumbing,dumbed,dumber,dumbs,dumbest) 

1. ADJ Someone who is dumb is completely unable to speak. 哑的 

例： ...a young deaf and dumb man. …一名年轻的聋哑人。 

2. ADJ If someone is dumb on a particular occasion, they cannot speak because they are angry, shocked, or surprised. 说不出话的 [文学性] [v-link ADJ] 

例： We were all struck dumb for a minute. 我们一时个个都哑口无言。 

3. ADJ If you call a person dumb , you mean that they are stupid or foolish. 蠢的 [非正式] 

例： The questions were set up to make her look dumb. 这些问题是安排好让她显得蠢的。 

4. ADJ If you say that something is dumb , you think that it is silly and annoying. 愚蠢而恼人的 [美国英语] [非正式] 

例： I came up with this dumb idea. 我想出了这个愚蠢而恼人的主意。

</div>

